the term six sigma was first utilized by motorola as a marketing ploy in helping them win the malcolm baldrige national quality award in  as part of winning the award all awardees must be open to presenting best practices to anyone who asks and the term six sigma was born it did not become popular until the mids after ge become successful in applying the motorola methodology and integrating six sigma into their own existing processes the all but forgotten fact is that back in  motorola was actually using the shewhart definition of plus and minus three standard deviations which was rejected by ford motor company in the early s because using that definition did not meet the requirements for the automotive industry which wasis plusminus four standard deviations for ongoing production products and plusminus five standard deviations for prototype products it wasnt until the late s that the term six sigma came to represent plusminus six standard deviations which it still means today however even this is not totally true as the six sigma proponents use a variation shifting factor calculation that reduces the theoretical value to something less than the true value of six standard deviations sources httpwwwasqorg httpwwwnistgov i lived this history and was the guy at ford who rejected the motorola process in the early s as well as being the training director for ford in the late s who lead training for  six sigma black belts sixsigmaboss ·  years ago  thumbs up  thumbs down report abuse  comment loading  add a comment submit · just now askers rating standard deviation joselyn ·  years ago  thumbs up  thumbs down report abuse comment add a comment submit · just now report abuse i think this question violates the community guidelines chat or rant adult content spam insulting other membersshow more i think this question violates the terms of service harm to minors violence or threats harassment or privacy invasion impersonation or misrepresentation fraud or phishing show more a